        kWantera's Kyle O'Connor promoted to Chief Executive Officer | kWantera - Energy Decision Intelligence
    

















Resources
Media, Materials, and More














        kWantera's Kyle O'Connor promoted to Chief Executive Officer
      

kWantera Inc., an energy technology company, today announced the promotion of Chief Commercial Officer Kyle O’Connor, 35, to the position of Chief Executive Officer, following Mark DeSantis, who stepped down as CEO. Mr. O’Connor will be responsible for driving kWantera’s growth trajectory and will lead the company’s ongoing product and commercialization journey. 
“The kWantera team is in great hands with Kyle given his extraordinary market orientation and expertise,” Mr. DeSantis stated. “I met Kyle in the spring of 2015 and I knew quickly that he had the ability to take this company to the next level.” 
“This is an exciting time for kWantera.  Our technology is helping more companies than ever make smarter energy choices.” said Mr. O’Connor. “Market deregulation has provided unprecedented transparency to electricity prices, but few tools to comprehend and capture the opportunity.  I’m proud to lead such a talented group of individuals committed to making a difference in the industry.”  
Mr. DeSantis stepped down as CEO in order to dedicate more time to the development of kWantix, LLC, an affiliate investment fund. Mr. DeSantis will continue to serve on the Boards of both kWantera and kWantix.
“We’re indebted to Mark for his tireless work ethic and passion for the company during the past nine years,” said Don Belt, Chairman of the Board of Directors. “We are equally excited that Mark will remain involved in kWantera’s future success.” 
ABOUT kWanterakWantera (www.kwantera.com) is a Pittsburgh-based company that uses advanced predictive analytics and machine learning to identify the optimal price, time and location at which to buy, sell or consume power in deregulated markets across North America and the world.







































