Home of the Day
        





 Sponsor Listing 



                    1334 Pennsylvania Avenue                




See All Homes of the Day





 











 Enlarge





                Mark DeSantis.            

                Joe Wojcik            








 



Mark DeSantis apparently is out at kWantera Inc., the Strip District-based provider of cost-saving energy management software and services that counts General Electric Co. as an investor.
According to the kWantera website, former GE executive Kyle O'Connor has taken the reins of the company as president and CEO. DeSantis, who led kWantera since 2008, is not included among 18 team members featured on its website.













 Enlarge






                            Mark DeSantis.                        
Joe Wojcik










 


DeSantis, O’Connor and CFO Matt Burlando did not respond to calls seeking comment. Donald Belt, chairman of kWantera's board, declined comment.




O’Connor joined kWantera last September as chief commercial officer, overseeing global sales, marketing, strategic partnerships and product development. He joined from GE (NYSE: GE), where he progressed through a series of business development posts, according to his LinkedIn profile, including managing director of commercial excellence.
GE invested$4.4 million in kWantera in late 2014, according to a filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission. In January 2015, Forbes ranked kWantera among its “10 Companies to Watch in Energy Analytics.”
DeSantis had a varied career prior to joining kWantera. He was an assistant to the late Sen. John Heinz, analyst in the administration of George H.W. Bush, director of government relations for Texas Instruments Inc. and ran for mayor of Pittsburgh as a Republican in 2007. He's also taught at Carnegie Mellon University since 1999.

Patty Tascarella covers banking, finance and the legal industry. Contact her at ptascarella@bizjournals.com or 412-208-3832.












 






